This paper deals with face recognition algorithms and their performance across different countries, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the issue of demographic bias, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the use of sampling strategies to balance the training procedure is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
